My dwarven spearman came upon some hills that were named something likeThe Joyous Hills of Knighting. I took a little nap there, since the namesounded innocent enough. When I woke up, I was bleeding profusely and bothof my arms were crippled, causing me to drop my spear and my shield. Theculprit was a little groundhog who was trying his damndest to kill me in mysleep. Reviewing the combat log later would reveal that he had passed outfrom over-exertion five or six times trying to nibble me to death. Soanyway, what does a prone dwarf with crippled arms do when confronted with asmall rodent hell-bent on trying to kill him?

You bite The groundhog in the head!
It is torn!
You latch on firmly to The groundhog's throat!
You shake The groundhog around by the throat!
The groundhog's throat has been torn out!
You break the grip of The groundhog's left rear leg on Your right hand.
The groundhog has bled to death.
